description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a Patient Safety Coordinator who will work within the DHU Health Care CIC Clinical Governance department supporting the NHS 111 First initiative. This is a new role to lead on the governance processes associated with the NHS 111 First initiative and the role will provide support in ensuring patient safety across the organisation. There have been a number of areas across England piloting the NHS 111 First initiative, which includes Portsmouth, Cornwall, and London. For the East Midlands, there will be a phased roll-out of NHS 111 First during autumn 2020.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To be successful in this role, you should have evidence of the following:-&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clinical professional qualification – first level registered nurse, other allied health professional&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Degree or equivalent qualification or equivalent experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Two years post registration qualification with a medical professional body&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Two years experience in a clinical governance / quality / risk management role&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sound knowledge of clinical governance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of consent and confidentiality&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working knowledge of clinical risk management, clinical governance, effectiveness and service quality issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Skilled in the use of computerised systems including Microsoft Office&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent organisational skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Effective diary &amp; time management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible &amp; adaptable&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to work effectively with a wide range of professional teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to collect, understand, analyse and summarise qualitative and numerical data&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent oral, written and communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to prioritise competing demands&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Creative problem solving with the ability to think laterally&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to prepare reports for a variety of audience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return for all the above, we offer:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive pay&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generous holiday entitlement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS Pension Scheme membership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The hours of work are 37.5hrs on a 6 month fixed term contract with a possibility of further extension, and a competitive salary of £25,000.00-£30,000.00 depending on experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameRosalind KibbleJob titleCorporate Head of Clinical/ Integrated GovernanceEmail addressrosalind.kibble@dhuhealthcare.nhs.ukTelephone number0300 1000 404&lt;/p&gt;
